{{TennisEventInfo|1985|Benson and Hedges Open| | date=7 – 14 January | edition=18th | prize_money=$80,000 | category=[[Grand Prix circuit|Grand Prix]] | draw=32S / 16D | surface=Hard / outdoor | location=[[Auckland]], New Zealand | champs={{flagicon|NZL}} [[Chris Lewis (tennis)|Chris Lewis]] <ref name="ms">{{cite web|title=1985 Auckland Men's Singles draw|url=http://www.atpworldtour.com/en/scores/archive/auckland/301/1985/draws?matchType=singles|publisher=[[Association of Tennis Professionals]] (ATP)}}</ref> | champd={{flagicon|AUS}} [[John Fitzgerald (tennis)|John Fitzgerald]] / {{flagicon|NZL}} [[Chris Lewis (tennis)|Chris Lewis]] <ref name="md">{{cite web|title=1985 Auckland Men's Doubles draw|url=http://www.atpworldtour.com/en/scores/archive/auckland/301/1985/draws?matchType=doubles|publisher=[[Association of Tennis Professionals]] (ATP)}}</ref> | main_name = Heineken Open (tennis){{!}} ATP Auckland Open }}
The '''1985 [[Heineken Open (tennis)|Benson and Hedges Open]]''' was a men's [[1985 Grand Prix (tennis)|Grand Prix]] [[tennis]] tournament played on outdoor hard courts in [[Auckland]], New Zealand. The tournament was held from 7 January to 14 January 1985. Seventh-seeded [[Chris Lewis (tennis)|Chris Lewis]] won the singles title.
==Finals==
===singles=== {{main article|1985 Benson and Hedges Open – Singles}} {{flagicon|NZL}} [[Chris Lewis (tennis)|Chris Lewis]] defeated {{flagicon|AUS}} [[Wally Masur]] 7–5, 6–0, 2–6, 6–4 * It was Lewis's second title of the year and the 11th of his career.
===doubles=== {{flagicon|AUS}} [[John Fitzgerald (tennis)|John Fitzgerald]] / {{flagicon|NZL}} [[Chris Lewis (tennis)|Chris Lewis]] defeated {{flagicon|AUS}} [[Broderick Dyke]] / {{flagicon|AUS}} [[Wally Masur]] 7–6, 6–2 * It was Fitzgerald's first title of the year and the 13th of his career. It was Lewis's first title of the year and the 10th of his career.
