{{Infobox venue | name = Kavak Sports Hall | nickname = | native_name = Kavak Spor Salonu | native_name_lang = | fullname = | former names = | logo_image = | logo_caption = | image = | image_size = | image_alt = | caption = | pushpin_map = Turkey | pushpin_mapsize = | pushpin_map_caption = Location of the sports hall in Turkey. | pushpin_label_position = | address = Yeni Cami Mah., OSB Sok. 7, Kavak | location = [[Kavak, Samsun|Kavak]], [[Samsun province|Samsun]], Turkey | coordinates = {{coord|41|05|02|N|36|02|36|E|type:landmark|display=inline,title}} | type = | genre = | broke_ground = 2014 | built = | opened = {{start date and age|2015}} | renovated = | expanded = | closed = | demolished = | owner = | operator = | surface = | scoreboard = | production = | cost = | architect = | builder = | project_manager = | structural engineer = | services engineer = | general_contractor = | main_contractors = | seating_type = | capacity = 578 | suites = | record_attendance = | dimensions = | field_shape = | acreage = | volume = | tenants = [[2017 Summer Deaflympics]] | embedded = | website = <!-- {{URL|example.com}} --> | publictransit = }}
'''Kavak Sports Hall''' ({{lang-tr|Kavak Spor Salonu}}) is a multi-purpose [[indoor arena|indoor sport venue]] located in [[Kavaki Samsun|Kavak]] district of [[Samsun Province]], northern Turkey.
The sports hall is situated in Yeni Cami Mah., OSB Sok. 7 in Kavak. The sports hall was built between 2014 and 2015. It covers an area of {{convert|2200|m2|sqft|abbr=on}} on a land of {{convert|5300|m2|sqft|abbr=on}}. It hosts basketball, handball and volleyball competitions,<ref name="skb"/> as well as archery,<ref name="h"/> karate,<ref name="ht1"/> and wrestling events.<ref name="d"/> The venue has a seating capacity for 578 spectators.<ref name="d"/>
==International events hosted== The venue will host [[freestyle wrestling|freestyle]] and [[Greco-Roman wrestling|Greco-Roman style]] wrestling events of the [[2017 Summer Deaflympics]].<ref name="d"/>
