{{Infobox stadium | name = Pavilhão Multiusos do Kilamba | nickname = Arena do Kilamba | logo_image = | logo_caption = | image = | caption = | fullname = | former_names = | location = [[Camama II]], [[Luanda]], Angola | coordinates = {{coord|-8.978635|13.283536|display=title|type:landmark}} | broke_ground = | built = | opened = {{Start date|2013|09|18}} | renovated = | expanded = | closed = | demolished = | owner = State-owned | operator = | surface = Hardwood | scoreboard = Electronic | cost = | architect = | project_manager = | structural engineer = | services engineer = | general_contractor = Omatapalo | main_contractors = | capacity = 12,720 | suites = | record_attendance = | dimensions = | acreage = | volume = | tenants = | embedded = | website = <!-- {{URL|example.com}} --> | publictransit = }}
The '''Pavilhão Multiusos do Kilamba''' (Multi-Use Pavilion of Kilamba), also called '''Arena do Kilamba''' (Kilamba Arena), is a state-owned multi-purpose indoor arena in [[Luanda]], Angola. The arena has a seating capacity of 12,720, and features hardwood flooring, electronic scoreboard and a wide range of features that make it one of the most modern of its kind in Africa. It is therefore fit for such sports as [[Basketball]], [[Team handball|Handball]], [[Volleyball]] and [[Roller Hockey]].<ref>{{cite web |url=https://desporto.sapo.pt/hoquei/mundial2013/artigo/2013/09/17/mundial_h_quei_patins_caracter_.html |title=Características técnicas do Pavilhão de Luanda |accessdate=2014-04-19|language=pt}}</ref>
The arena was specifically built to host the [[2013 FIRS Men's Roller Hockey World Cup|2013 Roller Hockey World Championship]]
The court is located in the [[Camama II]] neighborhood in Luanda, near the [[Kilamba|centralidade do Kilamba]], and across the road to the [[Estádio 11 de Novembro]].
