'''Sportsdigita''' is an American [[Technology in sports|sports technology]] firm headquartered in [[Minneapolis, Minnesota]]. It was founded in 2011 by ''Angelina Lawton'', former head of corporate communications for the [[Tampa Bay Lightning]]. Sportsdigita is the creator of the Digideck - an innovative online presentation tool built for the digital age. 

Sportsdigita combines a deep understanding of sports sponsorship, ticketing and premium experiences with best-in-class software technologies to solves business problems. The firm’s roster of blue chip clients consists of more than 300 professional and collegiate teams including Learfield and iconic franchises such as the [[New York Yankees]], [[Chicago Cubs|Chicago Cubs,]] [[Los Angeles Dodgers]], [[Boston Red Sox]], [[Cleveland Cavaliers]], [[Los Angeles Lakers]], [[Dallas Cowboys]] and [[Green Bay Packers]].

In 2015 entrepreneur and technology leader Cory Factor joined Sportsdigita as President. Factor is the former CEO of MinuteBids and a 2013 Minneapolis/St. Paul Business Journal 40 under 40 honoree.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.minutebids.com/cory-factor-ceo-of-minutebids-named-one-of-minneapolisst-paul-business-journal-2013-40-under-40/|title=Cory Factor, CEO of MinuteBids, named one of Minneapolis/St. Paul Business Journal 2013 40 Under 40|website=www.minutebids.com|accessdate=31 May 2017}}</ref>

Lawton is the wife of former professional hockey player, agent, manager and current on-air analyst for the NHL Network, [[Brian Lawton]].<ref>{{cite web|last1=Heitner|first1=Darren|title=Sportsdigita Shaking Up Sponsorship Scene With Its Digideck Platform|url=https://www.forbes.com/sites/darrenheitner/2013/07/20/sportsdigita-shaking-up-sponsorship-scene-with-its-digideck-platform/#10c637322d68|website=Forbes|accessdate=31 May 2017}}</ref>

