'''Willi Sten Railo''' (22 March 1941 – 8 July 2010) was a [[Norway|Norwegian]] [[Sport psychology|sport psychologist]] and professor of performance psychology.

He became known nationally for his 1986 book ''Best når det gjelder'' ("Best When it Counts"). Since the 1980s, he worked as a consultant for [[Sweden|Swedish]] [[Association football|football]] manager [[Sven-Göran Eriksson]], and continued in this position also during the latter's stint as manager for the [[England national football team|English national football team]]. He also worked with the Norwegian football club [[Vålerenga Football|Vålerenga]] in 2005, when the club won the [[Tippeligaen|Norwegian Premier League]].<ref name="AP">{{cite news|url=http://www.aftenposten.no/nyheter/sport/article3728888.ece|title=Willi Railo er død|work=[[Aftenposten]]|agency=[[Norwegian News Agency]]|language=Norwegian|accessdate=18 July 2010}}</ref> In the [[Norwegian Athletics Association]] he was a member of the medical committee in 1978 and 1980.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.friidrett.no/organisasjon/Documents/Historikk/Legeutvalget.htm|title=Legeutvalget|publisher=[[Norwegian Athletics Association]]|language=Norwegian|accessdate=18 July 2011|deadurl=yes|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20120509084820/http://www.friidrett.no/organisasjon/Documents/Historikk/Legeutvalget.htm|archivedate=9 May 2012|df=}}</ref>

